======================================================================
SUMMARY
======================================================================

CONFIRMED: Ω(T) has one vertex per DIRECTED odd cycle.
Multiple directed cycles on the same vertex set = multiple vertices.

The correct interpretation makes I(-1) ≤ 1 hold (so far).
The previous 'violations' were due to under-counting α₁
by treating vertex sets instead of directed cycles.

α₁ counts DIRECTED odd cycles, not vertex sets.
α₂ counts pairs of VERTEX-DISJOINT directed odd cycles.
(Two directed cycles on overlapping vertex sets are adjacent.)
